gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_BOOST: Displays the boost settings for this race. Boosts allow cars that are trailing to drive more quickly, giving them a chance to catch up. Three settings are available: None, Weak, and Strong.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_BOP_T: In races where BoP (Balance of Performance) is set to "On," weight and power are regulated to ensure that all cars are relatively equal. This does not happen if BoP is set to "Off".
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_CARS_: Displays the number of cars in this race.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_CATEG: Displays the category of cars that can be used for this race.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_COLLI: In races where collision penalties are set to "On," drivers will be penalized for colliding with other cars. If they are set to "Off," no penalties will be incurred for collisions.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_CONDI: Displays the weather for the race.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_DR_LI: Displays the Driver Rating (DR) restriction for this race. If there is no restriction, then anyone can participate. If "Min. X" is displayed, then only drivers with a DR of X or higher can join the race.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_DRIVE: Show required drivetrain for this race.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_EXPEC: Displays the expected number of pit stops, based on an average race. Factor this in when calculating the total duration of the race.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_FUEL_: Displays the rate at which fuel is consumed during the final race. When fuel consumption is set to "Off", no fuel will be consumed during the race. When fuel consumption is set to "X times", fuel will be consumed X times more quickly than normal.

Displays the rate at which fuel is consumed during qualifying. When fuel consumption is set to "Off", no fuel will be consumed during the race. When fuel consumption is set to "X times", fuel will be consumed X times more quickly than normal.
In races where fuel consumption is set to "Off," no fuel will be consumed during the race. In races where fuel consumption is set to "X times," fuel will be consumed X times more quickly than normal.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_LAPS_: Displays the number of laps in this race.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_LIMIT: Displays the amount of fuel that can be taken on board when changing tires at a pit stop. "X%" indicates that X% of a full tank can be taken on board at each pit stop.
Show max power limit set for this race.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_LOW_M: Set the extent to which driving off the track, for example on run-off areas, affects tires' grip. If this is set to "Low," then the level of grip will not be reduced as dramatically as in real life. If this is set to "Real," then areas outside the track will become extremely slippery, and you will even lose grip in the trackside "green zone".
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_MECHA: Displays whether mechanical damage can take place during this race. In races where mechanical damage can happen, impacts and collisions can affect a car's engine, suspension, or other parts. You may become unable to drive in a straight line, or you may develop engine trouble.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_NEED_: Show weight reduction limit set for this race.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_ONEMA: Display the cars that can enter this race.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_PIT_L: Displays the amount of time that is expected to be lost at a single pit stop. Factor this in when calculating the total duration of the race.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_PIT_S: Displays the minimum number of pit stops that have to be taken during this race. Some races do not require compulsory pit stops.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_RACE_: Displays the duration of an endurance race.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_REFUE: Displays a speed at which a car can be fueled. It is expressed in terms of how much fuel the car can take on board in one second.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_REQUI: Displays the type of tire that must be used when changing tires at a pit stop. Some races allow any type of tire to be used when changing at a pit stop.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_SETTI: In races where settings are "Adjustable," you can tweak various car settings to suit your style of driving and the track you're driving on. If settings are "Fixed," no such adjustments can be made.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_SHORT: Display the penalty for taking a shortcut across the track. Select "None" and no penalties will be incurred by drivers who take shortcuts. Select "Weak" or "Strong" to adjust the length of the time penalty incurred for taking shortcuts.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_SLIP_: Display the effectiveness of slipstream in this race. There are three settings available: "Real," "Weak," and "Strong". "Strong" has the strongest slipstream effect, while "Real" has the weakest. On the "Real" and "Weak" settings, not only is the reduction in air resistance less pronounced, you will also experience a loss of downforce. The slipstream refers to the pocket of reduced air resistance that is created behind a car in front of you. Making use of it in order to overtake is an established racing technique.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_SR_LI: Indicates the Sportsmanship Rating (SR) restriction for this race. If there is no restriction, then anyone can take part. If "Min. X" is displayed, then only drivers with an SR of X or higher can take part in the race.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_START: Display the start type for this race. The two main types are Grid Starts (where cars start from a stationary position) and Rolling Starts (where cars are already moving at the start of the race). Various options are available for both main start types.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_TIRE_: Displays the rate at which tires deteriorate during the final race. When tire wear is set to "Off", tires will not deteriorate at all during the race. When tire wear is set to "X times", tires will deteriorate X times more quickly than normal.

Displays the rate at which tires deteriorate during qualifying. When tire wear is set to "Off", tires will not deteriorate at all during the race. When tire wear is set to "X times", tires will deteriorate X times more quickly than normal.
In races where tire wear is set to "Off," tires will not deteriorate at all during the race. In races where tire wear is set to "X times," tires will deteriorate X times more quickly than normal.
Display the type of tire that can be used for this race.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_TOTAL: Display the total distance for this race.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_TRACK: Display the track limit, or the scope of the track area. Leaving the track area will incur a penalty. "Championship" track limits are stricter than "Normal" track limits, meaning it is easier to leave the track and incur a penalty.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.LABEL_USE_C: Display the category of cars that can be used for this race.
gt7sp.game.COMMON.RaceDetail.TITLE: Race Details
